BHHS C Dan Joyner - Office A

data.description: Nestled in the heart of Homeland Park within the prestigious Anderson County School District 5, this charming single-family ranch-style home offers a perfect blend of comfort and convenience. Boasting three bedrooms and two and a half baths, this residence provides ample space for family and guests. The welcoming interior features a well-designed layout, emphasizing both functionality and aesthetics. The heart of the home is a cozy living space, seamlessly connected to a modern kitchen. As you explore the home, you'll find a Primary bedroom with an en-suite bathroom, providing a private retreat. A huge Office/flex space next to the primary bedroom. Two additional bedrooms offer flexibility for a growing family. The two and a half baths ensure convenience for all. A distinctive feature of this property is the two-car attached carport, providing shelter for vehicles and additional storage space. The carport is not only practical but also adds to the overall aesthetic appeal of the home. The location within the renowned Anderson County School District 5 adds an extra layer of appeal, ensuring access to excellent educational opportunities for residents. Proximity to local amenities and parks. The roof has just recently been replaced.
